The neg agro from the concussion is not the agro of the spell, its the result.<br>
If you say that concussion does the deagro even if resisted is the same as when a nuke does full damage even if resisted.<br>
The result of the spell is the reduce of the agro. But the agro of the spell has to be a positive, since you can even pull with it. This pull agro has to come from something. If the spell would have 0 agro, you could not pull with it.<br>
<br>
Always see what is the result of a spell. And if a spell is resisted, the result cant come into effect.<br>
<br>
Other test:<br>
Look for a 100% immune magic mob. someone should do him some damage. Nuke the mob with SoS. You should have instant agro. Than chain cast concussion. The mob will not leave from you. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=elasto>Elasto</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Arcanist</span><br>  Posts: 1190<br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/8/03 4:14:14 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=25853.topic&index=24>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Wandor K</span><hr size=1> And for every post like the above you'll get a post from someone else saying there was no outside taunt or damage done yet a resisted concussion bounced a mob off of them to someone else. *shrugs*<br>
