<br>
Except that the aggro from all those things isn't part of the spell effect and the aggro reduction from the Concussion spell is. You get aggro from Concussion whether it is resisted or not, so that part works exactly the same as you state. In order for it to be the same as you are saying here, you would need to get damage from the nuke whether or not it was resisted, but you don't. You are taking two entirely seperate parts of the spell and trying to say they are the same, which doesn't work too well.<br>
<br>
&gt;See? I can make definitive statements without any proof too<br>
<br>
You need to work a bit on the definitive part though. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=4380">Qaman</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
