<br>
Lets look at it this way:  A nuke generates agro equivalent to it's max damage when resisted.  Try chain nuking a magic resistant mob and you'll see that's 100% true.<br>
<br>
So, if the agro adjustment of a nuke is calculated before resist, why would concussion be any different?<br>
<br>
The easiest to see illustration is when I'm in a group with a poor agro control warrior MA.  I get summoned, I concussion and the far majority of the time as soon as the concussion is resisted the agro goes back to the MA.  This is not spacing out nukes like you're casting a concussion, this is casting after I have agro and agro immediately being lost after the spell is resisted.<br>
<br>
I don't know if this patch has changed the way in which concussion works.  It is apparent that some things have been changed with agro in respect to ranged attacks.  They planned to bump up agro on Rangers, so possibly agro is being calculated as total damage dealt rather than off the spell max.  If so we're gonna be pretty messed up for a while. <p><table width="320" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">
